HEADWORD: Acotyledonous
<hw>A*cot`y*led"on*ous</hw> <pr>(#; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having
no seed lobes, as the dodder; also applied to plants which have no true
seeds, as ferns, mosses, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Acouchy</ent>⟦br⟧
